<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About Us</title>
    <link href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.15.3/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons/font/bootstrap-icons.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        .bg-custom {
            background: #f8f9fa;
        }
        .list-icon {
            color: #007bff;
            margin-right: 10px;
        }
        .color-theme {
            color: #007bff;
        }
        .shadow-custom {
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .rounded-custom {
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container my-5">
        <h1 class="text-center color-theme mb-4">About Us</h1>
        
        <div class="bg-white p-5 shadow-custom rounded-custom">
            <p class="lead">
                <strong>The United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF)</strong> is a United Nations agency responsible for providing humanitarian and developmental aid to children worldwide. Established on December 11, 1946, after World War II, UNICEF was originally created to provide emergency food and healthcare to children in countries that had been devastated by the war. Over the years, its mission has expanded to address the long-term needs of children and mothers in developing countries.
            </p>

            <h4 class="mt-4">Key Areas of Work:</h4>

            <div class="mt-3">
                <h5>
                    <i class="bi bi-heart-fill list-icon"></i> Health and Nutrition:
                </h5>
                <ul class="list-unstyled ml-3">
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Vaccination campaigns to prevent diseases like polio and measles.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Programs to combat malnutrition through the distribution of nutrient-rich foods and supplements.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Initiatives to promote maternal health and safe childbirth practices.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-3">
                <h5>
                    <i class="bi bi-book-fill list-icon"></i> Education:
                </h5>
                <ul class="list-unstyled ml-3">
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Building and rehabilitating schools in underserved areas.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Providing learning materials and training teachers.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Advocating for inclusive education policies to ensure all children, especially girls and children with disabilities, can access education.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-3">
                <h5>
                    <i class="bi bi-droplet-fill list-icon"></i> Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH):
                </h5>
                <ul class="list-unstyled ml-3">
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Installing clean water systems and sanitation facilities in schools and communities.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Promoting hygiene practices to prevent the spread of diseases.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Emergency WASH services in disaster-affected areas.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-3">
                <h5>
                    <i class="bi bi-shield-fill list-icon"></i> Child Protection:
                </h5>
                <ul class="list-unstyled ml-3">
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Programs to prevent child trafficking, exploitation, and child labor.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Initiatives to support children in conflict zones and those affected by violence.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Efforts to strengthen child protection systems and legal frameworks.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-3">
                <h5>
                    <i class="bi bi-lightning-fill list-icon"></i> Emergency Response:
                </h5>
                <ul class="list-unstyled ml-3">
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Rapid response teams that provide immediate relief in the wake of natural disasters and conflicts.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Distribution of emergency supplies such as food, water, shelter, and medical care.</li>
                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle list-icon"></i> Long-term support to help communities rebuild and recover.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@popperjs/core@2.9.2/dist/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
